-- Equity Bank Shares Gains for a Second Day: Nairobi Mover
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2012-03-21T14:37:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/equity-bank-shares-gains-for-a-second-day-nairobi-mover.html
Equity Bank Ltd. (EQBNK) ,  Kenya ’s biggest
lender by customers, climbed a second day.  The stock advanced as much as 3.2 percent before trading
0.9 percent higher at 17.6 shillings at the end of trading in
Nairobi.  “The fundamentals of the bank are still good and it has
had phenomenal growth in the last five years and management
believe it can double assets every five years,” Poonam Vora, an
analyst at Nairobi-based Dyer & Blair Investment Bank Ltd., said
in a phone interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net . 